my Awards|Creative Arts Emmy Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|September 9, 2018\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Guest Actor in a Comedy Series|Outstanding Guest Actor in a Comedy Series]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Stunt Coordination for a Comedy Series or Variety Program\n| ''Brooklyn Nine-Nine''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Critics' Choice Television Awards]]\n| [[9th Critics' Choice Television Awards|January 13, 2019]]\n| [[Critics' Choice Television Award for Best Actor in a Comedy Series|Best Actor in a Comedy Series]]\n| Andy Samberg\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Edgar Allan Poe Awards]]\n| April 25, 2019\n| Best Television Episode Teleplay\n| Luke Del Tredici (Episode: \"The Box\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Shorty Awards]]\n| [[11th Shorty Awards|May 5, 2019]]\n| Best TV Show\n| ''Brooklyn Nine-Nine''\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Gracie Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|May 21, 2019\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Outstanding Actress in a Supporting Role - Comedy or Musical\n| Stephanie Beatriz\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Chelsea Peretti\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|[[Imagen Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"3\"|August 10, 2019\n| Best Primetime Program - Comedy\n| ''Brooklyn Nine-Nine''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Best Supporting Actress - Television\n| Stephanie Beatriz\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Melissa Fumero\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Teen Choice Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[2019 Teen Choice Awards|August 11, 2019]]\n| Choice Comedy TV Show\n| ''Brooklyn Nine-Nine''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Choice Comedy TV Actor\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Andy Samberg\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Gold Derby Awards\n| rowspan=\"2\"|September 17, 2019\n| Best Comedy Actor\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Comedy Guest Actor\n| [[Lin-Manuel Miranda]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[GLAAD Media Award]]s\n| [[31st GLAAD Media Awards|March 19, 2020 and April 16, 2020]]\n| Outstanding Comedy Series\n| ''Brooklyn Nine-Nine''\n| {{pending}}\n|}\n\n==Broadcast==\n''Brooklyn Nine-Nine'' is broadcast in Canada on [[City (TV network)|City]]. After the second episode of the second season, it was replaced on Sunday nights by ''[[NHL on Sportsnet#Hometown Hockey|Rogers Hometown Hockey]]'' for the duration of the [[2014\u201315 NHL season#Regular season|2014\u201315 NHL regular season]]; after the NHL season concluded City resumed airing ''Brooklyn Nine-Nine'', and has continued to broadcast the show [[Simultaneous substitution|simultaneously with the American broadcast]] since the third season (''Hometown Hockey'' was moved to [[Sportsnet]] in 2015). In the United Kingdom, the show premiered on [[E4 (TV channel)|E4]] in January 2014.<ref>{{cite web|last=Tartaglione|first=Nancy|title=Global Showbiz Briefs: 'Brooklyn Nine-Nine' To UK's Channel 4; Henry Winkler-Penned Kids Books In TV Deal; 'Voice UK': More|url=https://www.deadline.com/2013/09/global-showbiz-briefs-brooklyn-nine-nine-to-uks-channel-4-henry-winkler-penned-kids-books-in-tv-deal-voice-uk-more/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=September 20, 2013|date=September 20, 2013}}</ref> The second season debuted on January 15, 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvwise.co.uk/2014/12/e4-sets-uk-premiere-date-broklyn-nine-nine-season-2/|title=E4 Sets UK Premiere Date For 'Brooklyn Nine-Nine' Season 2|date=December 18, 2014|work=TV Wise|accessdate=February 13, 2015}}</ref> the third began on January 7, 2016 and the fourth on January 5, 2017 with the fifth on March 8, 2018, the sixth on March 28, 2019 and the seventh on March 26, 2020. The series airs on [[RT\u00c9 Two]] in Ireland. In New Zealand, ''Brooklyn Nine-Nine'' premiered on [[TV2 (New Zealand)|TV2]] on February 13, 2014.\n\nIn South Asia, ''Brooklyn Nine-Nine'' airs on [[Comedy Central India]]. In Australia, it premiered on [[SBS One|SBS]] on July 28, 2014, and airs repeats on [[Universal Channel (Australia)|Universal Channel]] from January 7, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/universalchannelaustralia/photos/a.198562680221159.47103.168417453235682/732996863444402/?type=1&theater|title=Timeline Photos \u2013 Universal Channel Australia \u2013 Facebook|work=facebook.com}}</ref> It moved to [[SBS Two|SBS 2]] in 2015<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2015/02/brooklyn-nine-nine-to-switch-to-sbs-2.html|title=Brooklyn Nine-Nine to switch to SBS 2|last=Knox|first=David|date=February 7, 2015|work=TV Tonight|accessdate=February 13, 2015}}</ref> commencing with the second season, which premiered on March 3, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2015/02/returning-brooklyn-nine-nine.html|title=Returning: Brooklyn Nine-Nine|last=Knox|first=David|date=February 25, 2015|work=TV Tonight|accessdate=March 6, 2015}}</ref> It has now moved to [[SBS Viceland]], currently airing on Fridays at 8:30pm. In December 2014, [[Netflix|Netflix UK]] added the first season of ''Brooklyn Nine-Nine'' to its listings, with Netflix Australia following suit in March 2015. Since 2016 Netflix Germany/Austria/Switzerland carries season 1 to 5 in both English and German audio. In South East Asia and Sri Lanka, ''Brooklyn Nine-Nine'' airs right after the U.S. on [[Diva (Asia TV channel)|Diva]].<ref>[http://www.divatv.asia/brooklyn-9-9-season-3=]{{dead link|date=October 2016}}</ref>\nSince June 2019, Netflix in Latin America has seasons 1 to 5.<ref>{{ cite web |url=https://www.ar.marca.com/claro/trending/2019/05/27/5cebf532ca4741ed7c8b459b.html |title=Netflix estrenos de Junio |work=Netflix |accessdate= September 3, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Adaptation===\nThe first adaptation of the series, ''Escouade 99'', will be set in [[Quebec City]]. ''Escouade 99'' has a budget of 4 million for the first season of the series, which is approximately the same budget of a single episode of ''Brooklyn Nine-Nine''. <ref>{{cite web |url=https://ici.radio-canada.ca/amp/1497419/premieres-images-tournage-adaptation-quebecoise-brooklyn-nine-nine | title = Premi\u00e8res images du tournage de l\u2019adaptation qu\u00e9b\u00e9coise de Brooklyn Nine-Nine | language = French | trans-title = First images from the filming of the Quebec adaptation of Brooklyn Nine-Nine | date = 29 January 2020 | work = Radio-Canada.ca | publisher = Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 Radio\u2011Canada | accessdate = 2 February 2020}}</ref> The show is slated to air in summer 2020 on Qu\u00e9bec streaming platform [[Club Illico]].\n\n==Home media==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"4%\"| Complete season\n! colspan=\"3\" width=\"20%\"| DVD Release Date\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"5%\"| Special Features\n|-\n! Region 1\n! Region 2\n! Region 4\n|-\n! Season 1\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | September 23, 2014\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | September 29, 2014\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | December 11, 2014\n| rowspan=\"6\"| Deleted Scenes\n|-\n! Season 2\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | September 8, 2015\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | September 28, 2015\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | September 3, 2015\n|-\n! Season 3\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | August 23, 2016\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | August 22, 2016\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | September 29, 2016\n|-\n! Season 4\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | August 22, 2017\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | September 4, 2017\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | September 20, 2017\n|-\n! Season 5\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | August 28, 2018\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | November 19, 2018\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | September 19, 2018\n|-\n! Season 6\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | August 20, 2019\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | August 26, 2019\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | August 28, 2019\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{sisterlinks|display=''Brooklyn Nine-Nine''|d=Q13417244|n=no|b=no|v=no|voy=no|c=Category:Brooklyn Nine-Nine|s=no|wikt=no|species=no|m=no|mw=no}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* [https://www.fox.com/brooklyn-nine-nine/ Page from Fox]\n* {{IMDb title|2467372}}\n\n{{sequence\n|prev=''[[Elementary (TV series)|Elementary]]''<br />[[Super Bowl XLVII|